	<h2>Support The Public</h2>
	<div class="Content">

		<p>
			Since the days of Joseph Papp, a distinct group of individuals have partnered with us to help produce The Public's diverse array of productions and programs. Since over 75% of the annual budget comes from the generosity of our donors, your support helps ensure the development and expansion of The Public's unique, challenging productions, educational initiatives, and free and reduced cost programming.
		</p>
		<section>
			<img src="/media/unmanaged/images/photos/youngpartners.jpg" alt="Photo of members of the Partners Program" class="FloaterB" />
			<h3>
				<a href="/partners">Public Theater Partners Program</a>
			</h3>
			<p>
				Support The Public Theater by becoming a Public Theater Partner.  As a Partner, you will help ensure the development and expansion of our educational outreach programming, free and low-cost ticketing initiatives, and Shakespeare in the Park. In thanks for your gift, you will receive priority seating for Shakespeare in the Park, complimentary tickets throughout the season, and invitations to special events.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section>
			<img src="/media/unmanaged/images/photos/partners.jpg" alt="Photo of members of the Young Partners Program" class="FloaterA" />
			<h3>
				<a href="http://youngpartners.publictheater.org">Young Partners</a>
			</h3>
			<p>
				Our Young Partners are a dynamic group of New Yorkers in their 20s and 30s who share a passion for The Public Theater’s mission to make great art accessible to all. By supporting The Public Theater as a Young Partner, you will be invited to parties, plays, discussions and performances with up-and-coming actors, writers, directors, musicians, artists, and art-lovers alike.
			</p>
		</section>
